</P>
<P>
 Always ready to take on a hot potatoe: Former Vice President Dan Quayle will 
be one of the guests this morning at a conference about political humor titled, 
"Do Conservatives Have a Sense of Humor?" 
</P>
<P>
 The event is at that Simi Valley laugh factory -- the Ronald Reagan 
Presidential Library. 
</P>
<P>
 Quayle, who has a new book out, has been very visible lately and we think we 
know why. During the 1992 presidential campaign, he was asked by CNN's Bernard 
Shaw about his own presidential prospects. 
</P>
<P>
 Quayle responded: "Let us see George Bush reelected . . . and then we'll talk 
about 1994." 
</P>
<P>
 Good luck in November, Dan. 
</P>
<P>
