<HEADLINE>
<P>
BICYCLE SAFETY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While it is good to learn that the California Highway Patrol is concerned 
about bicyclist safety (May 1), why does CHP place the responsibility for 
safety on bicyclists? Aren't they aware that almost all bicyclists seriously 
injured or killed were hit by cars? 
</P>
<P>
 Doesn't the CHP bear some responsibility for preventing these collisions? The 
CHP should work toward deterring dangerous motorist behavior, which would 
benefit everyone: cyclists, pedestrians, motorcyclists and other motorists. 
</P>
<P>
 PETER JACOBSEN 
</P>
<P>
 Safety Committee Chairman 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County Bicycle Coalition 
