NEWSWIRE: MOTOR SPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Drivers, engineers and team officials involved in Formula One racing have 
agreed to accept safety changes decreed by the sports's governing body, the 
International Automobile Federation (FIA).The changes, designed to reduce 
speeds, will take effect at the next Formula One race, the Spanish Grand Prix 
at Barcelona May 29. Names in the News 
</P>
<P>
 Roland Street, 54, of Hailey, Ida., the father of Olympic downhill silver 
medalist Picabo Street, pleaded guilty to beating his wife, Dee, 47, in a 
domestic dispute May 9. Street will be sentenced June 6. He was ordered to stay 
away from his wife and from Tim Coles, described as a friend of Mrs. Street. 
