<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Derya Buyukuncu 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Swimming / Sprinter 
</P>
<P>
 Buyukuncu set three Division I records, one of which broke his national prep 
record in the 100-yard backstroke, at the Southern Section Division I finals.He 
won the 50 free in a section-record 20.27 seconds, the 100 back in 47.50 and 
helped the Warriors to victories in the 200 medley relay and the 400 free 
relay. In the 400 relay, he swam the first 100 in 43.85, breaking the record of 
44.27 set by Mission Viejo's Eric Diehl. "A 43, I never thought I'd see a high 
school kid do that," Woodbridge Coach Dan Gaines said. "My heart's still 
pounding thinking about it." Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Brett Hankey, Mater Dei, beat previously undefeated Johnny France of El 
Toro, 7-5, 6-0, to win the South Coast League singles tennis title. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mark Kwok, Laguna Hills, won the 100 butterfly in 50.41 seconds and the 200 
IM in 1:51.49 at the Division III swimming championships. 
</P>
<P>
 * Brian Laske and Kiet Tran, Los Amigos, each had 33 kills in a five-game 
victory over Foothill in a Division II playoff match. 
</P>
<P>
 * Tyce Routson, El Toro, won the section Division I diving title with a 
section-record 604.95 points. 
</P>
