<P>
 Softball / Pitcher-first base 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park, hoping for a share of the Century League title, needed Foothill to 
falter last week.The Knights didn't, but the Spartans came through with two 
victories to keep the pressure on. McArthur was in the thick of things in both 
games. She was three for four with a home run and four runs batted in in an 8-2 
victory over Santa Ana Valley and pitched a one-hitter with 10 strikeouts in a 
1-0 victory over Canyon, which knocked the Comanches out of the playoffs. "We 
needed two wins and she helped us however she could," Spartan Coach David 
Shelton said. Other notables: 
