<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: KIM OUT OF SECTION SINGLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunny Hills sophomore Kevin Kim has pulled out of the Southern Section singles 
tournament so he can practice for his upcoming stretch of clay-court 
tournaments. Kim, the No. 1-ranked boys' 16 player in the nation, did not play 
in the section individual tournament last year because of an injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim competed in the Freeway League tournament, the section individual 
qualifying tournament, and defeated teammate Joseph Gilbert, 6-0, 6-2, in the 
final. 
</P>
<P>
 "I played league because my coach (Steve White) wanted me to," Kim said. 
</P>
<P>
 But Kim said he had already decided to prepare for three upcoming clay-court 
tournaments by practicing at Sherwood Country Club in Thousand Oaks May 26-30, 
the same weekend of the section individual tournament at SeaCliff Tennis Club 
in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 In the next two months, Kim will play on the red clay of Italy and France with 
other top-ranked players in the boys' 16 division. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
