<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; ATLANTIC TO NAME EX-SONY EXEC TO TOP SALES JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Sony Music executive Pete Anderson is expected to be named today as 
vice president of sales for Atlantic Records. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson will oversee the daily operations of Atlantic's sales business both 
nationally and regionally.Anderson most recently was Sony Music's Los Angeles 
branch manager. He also is the former vice president of sales at Sony's Epic 
Records unit, overseeing sales of such artists as Pearl Jam and Celine Dion. 
</P>
<P>
 * Former LIVE entertainment executive David Penner was named chief financial 
officer for Malibu Comics. 
</P>
<P>
 * Joanie Kamuca has been named vice president and general manager, East Coast 
administration, for MCA Music Entertainment Group. Separately, Fred Silber was 
named vice president of business affairs for MCA Music Publishing. 
</P>
<P>
 * Maria Isabel Perez has joined USA Networks as publicist, corporate andmedia 
relations. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sara Colleton, a producer on the upcoming film "Renaissance Man," has 
entered a long-term production arrangement with Touchstone Pictures. 
</P>
<P>
 * MCA Music named Gayle Moore vice president of financial administration. 
Separately, MCA's Winterland Productions named John Crist vice president of 
sales and John Barrows senior vice president of sales and marketing. 
</P>
