<P>
BASEBALL; FOUR O.C. TEAMS BEGIN PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four Orange County baseball teams begin play today in Southern Section 
wild-card playoff games. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division II, Savanna will be at Cerritos, the third-place team from the San 
Gabriel Valley League. In Division III, Century will be at Irvine and Garden 
Grove will be at La Mirada Glenn, the third-place team from the Suburban 
League. 
</P>
<P>
 First-round games begin Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley was the No. 1-seeded team in Division I. A top-seeded team has 
not won that division since Lakewood in 1970. 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta, which lost in the Division III title game last season, is the 
second-seeded team in the division this year. Defending division Tustin is 
seeded fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's is the second-seeded team in Division VI. CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
