<P>
 "The Who's Tommy" grossed $928,103 -- 99.62% of capacity -- for eight 
performances May 10 through 15 at the Orange County Performing Arts Center in 
Costa Mesa. Although the show didn't set a house attendance record ("Les 
Miserables" and "Grease" have done better), the gross for "Tommy" was the 
highest one-week total of the show's national tour so far, according to a 
center spokesman. 
