<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; SUSPECT 
ARRESTED IN FATAL CARJACKING; 2ND SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A suspect has been arrested in the carjacking murder of a father of three in 
Willowbrook, and the victim's classic lowrider car has been recovered, Los 
Angeles County sheriff's deputies said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives responding to an anonymous tip arrested Leland Chambers, 31, as he 
attempted to drive the stolen 1970 Chevrolet Impala convertible away from an 
apartment building in Lynwood, Deputy Gabriel Ramirez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ramirez said detectives had gotten a telephone call a few minutes earlier that 
the meticulously customized car, covered with blankets, was parked behind the 
apartment building in the 3300 block of Carlin Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said they were looking for a second suspect in the slaying of 
Terrance Booker, 26, of Gardena. 
</P>
<P>
 Booker -- a pharmacy employee with children ages 4, 6 and 8 -- was accosted by 
two men after he delivered groceries to a friend in an apartment on El Segundo 
Boulevard shortly after 10 a.m. Sunday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives said that although Booker apparently did nothing to stop the men 
from taking the car, one of them suddenly opened fire. Hit once in the upper 
body, Booker tried to run, making it almost all the way across the broad 
boulevard before he collapsed on the pavement and died. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said one of the assailants drove off in Booker's car and the other 
followed in a blue sports coupe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
