<P>
SAN DIEGO STATE HIRES JC COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fred Trenkle, a highly successful junior college coach in Idaho, Monday was 
named basketball coach at San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
 Trenkle was given a five-year contract to try to revive San Diego State, which 
has had nine consecutive losing seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Trenkle was 329-34 from 1983 to 1993 at the College of Southern Idaho, which 
reached the national JC tournament eight consecutive seasons and won it in 
1987. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's going to be a challenge," Trenkle said. "It's going to be a little bit 
different than what I've been used to. . . . I've never been a loser, and I'm 
not going to start now." 
</P>
<P>
 Trenkle, 45, replaces Tony Fuller, who took over at Pepperdine on May 5. 
</P>
