<P>
 An Oxnard police officer suffered minor injuries Monday afternoon when a man 
driving a pickup truck pulled in front of the officer's motorcycle, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officer Joseph Johnson, 35, was driving west on 5th Street when Ruben Gomez, 
31, of Oxnard drove out of an alley at A Street in front of the officer, police 
said. Johnson attempted to avoid the collision, but broadsided the pickup. 
</P>
