EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; CITY GETS 4 DEPUTIES TO FILL VACANCIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four Ventura County sheriff's deputies have been shifted to covering the city 
of Moorpark to fill vacancies left by those who were promoted or transferred to 
other positions in the department, sheriff's officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Deputy Tim Cowgill, a 14-year veteran who has worked in Camarillo and 
the County Jail, was moved to Moorpark to become patrol supervisor, Sgt. Keith 
Parks said. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark will also get two new patrol officers -- Deputy Jody Keller, a 
13-year veteran who has worked in the Custody Division, and Deputy Jerry Gomez, 
who completed patrol orientation in Moorpark after working for three years at 
the County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 The department also transferred Deputy Larry Bull from Thousand Oaks to 
Moorpark, where he will work as a detective on the 22-member force, Parks said. 
</P>
<P>
 Parks said the department is still waiting for two patrol deputies to finish 
training so that they can fill vacancies in Moorpark that are being covered on 
an overtime basis by deputies from other details. 
