be better off by 1998, up from 56% in November.The survey of 366 executives at 
companies with more than $1 million in sales or revenue was conducted by 
telephone from April 27 to May 4 at a wide range of companies, based on 
interviews with presidents, chief executives or owners. The margin of error was 
5%. 
