<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hughes to Sell Satellite to Malaysia: The Far East nation today is expected to 
buy its first telecommunications satellite from Hughes Aircraft Co.Terms were 
not disclosed, but the HS 376 satellite -- to be built in El Segundo -- 
typically costs between $50 million and $100 million. It will provide Malaysia 
with direct satellite-to-home television broadcast capabilities. Hughes in the 
past two years has sold 12 satellites that serve the Far East, which is Hughes' 
fastest-growing market, said Steven D. Dorfman, president of the company's 
telecommunications and space group. 
</P>
