<P>
 Continental Expands 'Peanuts Fares': The airline, stepping up expansion of its 
no-frills, short-haul service, said it will offer unrestricted, low-cost 
"Peanuts Fares" on 292 more of its daily flights.The carrier also plans to hire 
up to 400 pilots in the next 12 months to keep up with its growing flight 
schedule. Houston-based Continental Airlines, the fifth-largest U.S. carrier, 
now employs about 4,000 pilots. "What you're seeing is only the beginning of 
what ultimately will be a revision of the industry's fare structure," said Tom 
Longman of Bear Stearns & Co. 
