REGIONAL PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * James Ward was named president and chief executive of Advanced Photonix Inc. 
Previously, Ward was president of Ling Electronics Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 He replaces Thomas T. Lewis, who was named chairman.Lewis replaces Bernhardt 
Denmark, who remains on the board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo-based Advanced Photonix Inc. makes electronic photo-detection 
devices. 
</P>
<P>
 * William H. Comte has been named chief executive officer of the 
Encino-Trazana Regional Medical Center and the North Hollywood Medical Center, 
both of which are owned by American Medical International Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 Comte succeeds Roger Drue, who left recently to head a hospital in Hawaii. 
Comte came from Birmingham, Ala., where he was senior vice president for the 
Medical Center Division of Healthsouth Rehabilitation Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 * WellPoint Health Networks Inc., a Woodland Hills-based managed health-care 
company, has appointed Yon Y. Jorden as chief financial officer. Joren was 
named acting chief financial officer in August and previously was WellPoint's 
vice president and controller. Before joining WellPoint, Jorden was vice 
president and controller of Blue Cross of California, the nonprofit parent 
company of WellPoint. 
</P>
<P>
 * Summit Care Corp. in Burbank announced changes to its board as a result of 
the merger of Summit Health Ltd. into OrNda HealthCorp. Donald J. Amaral, 41, 
president and chief operating officer of OrNda, will assume the post of 
chairman of the board of Summit Care, replacing Don Freeberg, 69, who has 
resigned. 
</P>
<P>
 William C. Scott, 56, president of Summit Care since 1985, has assumed the 
additional post of chief executive officer, which had been held by Amaral. 
Keith B. Pitts, 36, executive vice president and chief financial officer of 
OrNda HealthCorp, has been named to the board, replacing John Anderson, 76, who 
also resigned. 
</P>
