<HEADLINE>
<P>
BODY WATCH; TIPS FOR OLDER ORTHODONTIC PATIENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN O. RYAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Orthodontic treatment must begin with a healthy mouth. See a dentist to make 
sure everything is in good shape. 
</P>
<P>
 * Older patients take longer to heal, so they should think long and hard about 
treatments that include major jaw surgery. 
</P>
<P>
 * Patients taking special medications need to let the orthodontist know 
beforehand because certain medications can interfere with movement of the 
teeth. 
</P>
<P>
 * In cases where patients have had missing teeth for many years, sometimes 
part of the bone structure has lost some width and height, limiting how far the 
teeth can be moved. KATHLEEN O. RYAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
