<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: MANILA; THRILLA IN MANILA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the second staging of the pageant in the Philippines, 77 contestants will 
compete Saturday for the title of Miss Universe at Manila's Philippine 
International Convention Center.The internationally televised pageant was first 
held in the Philippine capital in 1974 under the patronage of then-First Lady 
Imelda Marcos, herself a former beauty queen. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1993, Dayanara Torres of Puerto Rico won the title. The Philippines has 
produced two winners. This year's Filipina candidate is Charlene Gonzales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
