CHINA DISSIDENT HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police detained prominent Chinese dissident Wang Dan today after he was 
interviewed by foreign journalists who came to his home, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 At least five police officers showed Wang a detention warrant about 11 a.m. 
and took him away, a family member told Reuters. 
</P>
<P>
 Wang had been detained twice in the week before Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher's March visit to Beijing. 
</P>
<P>
 Wang was imprisoned after the 1989 Tian An Men Square crackdown and paroled 3 
1/2 years later. 
