<HEADLINE>
<P>
WATSON OKS BUYING BIO-SEPARATION LTD. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Watson General Corp., an environmental services company, said Monday that it 
has signed a letter of intent to acquire a controlling interest in 
Bio-Separation Ltd., a privately held British company. 
</P>
<P>
 Bio-Separation holds a worldwide patent on a process that uses microorganisms 
and magnetic separation to remove heavy metal contaminants from water, Watson 
said. The British company was purchased with about 76,500 Watson common shares, 
or $353,813 at Monday's market value. The stock closed at $4.625 a share, up 
37.5 cents, in Nasdaq trading. 
</P>
<P>
 Watson, based in Irvine, monitors 3,500 underground storage tanks with a 
remote system and provides environmental consulting, site remediation and 
on-site mobile antifreeze recycling services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
