<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: HARMONY HOLDINGS REPORTS $120,505 PROFIT IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harmony Holdings Inc., the Burbank producer of television commercials and 
music videos, reported a profit of $120,505 for the third quarter that ended 
March 31, in contrast to a loss of $713,387 in the first quarter the previous 
year. The turnaround was on a revenue increase of 68% to $12.28 million from 
$7.30 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months that ended March 31, the company's loss widened to $1.87 
million, compared with a loss of $1.48 million reported for the same period a 
year before. Revenue for the nine months was $31.96 million, 83% higher than 
$17.49 million the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the first-quarter results to an increase in the number 
of commercials it produced and to restructuring. 
</P>
</TEXT>
