<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: FORTUNE PETROLEUM'S LOSS WIDENS IN 1ST QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fortune Petroleum Corp., an Agoura Hills oil and gas exploration and 
production company, said its first-quarter loss widened to $135,000 compared 
with a loss of $70,000 in the same period a year earlier.Revenue was $812,000 
for the quarter that ended March 31, up 49% from $545,000 the year before. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the results in part to increased production. The 
company has also said it is responding to falling oil prices by spending more 
for natural gas exploration. 
</P>
