<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: BIOSOURCE'S INCOME UP SLIGHTLY IN 1ST QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BioSource International Inc., the Camarillo-based supplier of biomedical 
research products, said its net income for the first quarter that ended March 
31 was $162,463, up slightly from $160,216 in the same quarter a year earlier. 
Revenue in the first quarter increased 22% to $1.54 million from $1.26 million 
the year before. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it reduced its administrative and selling costs from the 
first quarter last year, and more than doubled spending for research and 
development. 
</P>
