<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: LESLIE'S POOLMART LOSES $3.57 MILLION IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Leslie's Poolmart, a Chatsworth retailer of swimming pool supplies, reported a 
first-quarter loss of $3.57 million compared with a loss of $3.63 million a 
year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Sales for the quarter ended March 31 were up 14% to $13.3 million from $11.6 
million in the comparable period a year earlier. The company usually has 
significant losses in the first quarter because swimming pool products are in 
low demand during the winter. 
</P>
