<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: FLAMEMASTER POSTS $31,745 LOSS ON REVENUE DECLINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Flamemaster Corp., a Sun Valley maker of industrial sealants, adhesives and 
coatings, reported a $31,745 net loss for its fiscal second quarter ended March 
31 on a 28% decline in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The company blamed the loss on decreased royalties from Europe, a lack of 
product development fees and legal expenses in its antitrust lawsuit against 
Courtaulds PLC, a competitor and Flamemaster's largest shareholder with a 
nearly 26% stake.The Northridge earthquake also hurt the company's results, it 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 A year earlier, Flamemaster earned $123,540. Its revenue in the latest quarter 
was $638,637, down from $890,688 a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, the company's earnings fell 64%, to $68,668 from $189,737 
in the same period last year. Its revenue was $1.49 million, down 6% from $1.59 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
