<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CHEESECAKE FACTORY'S PROFIT UP 45% IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cheesecake Factory Inc., the Calabasas-based restaurant chain, said its 
first-quarter profit increased 45% as revenue rose 36%, but the earnings were 
slightly lower than analysts' expectations. 
</P>
<P>
 In the quarter ended March 31, the company posted earnings of $1.3 million, up 
from $897,000 a year earlier.Revenue rose to $18.7 million from $13.8 million. 
However, the earnings were slightly lower than expectations on Wall Street, 
which further depreciated the company's stock. 
</P>
<P>
 Cheesecake Factory operates eight restaurants in California, Washington, D.C., 
and Atlanta. It has three restaurants under construction in Bethesda, Md., 
Miami and Chicago, and completed a lease for one in Boca Raton, Fla. The 
company said it is also completing lease negotiations for additional 
restaurants in Houston and Las Vegas and signed a letter of intent to open a 
restaurant in Boston. 
</P>
