</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
May 17, 1994, Tuesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Page 8 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
68 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: REXHALL INDUSTRIES POSTS $520,000 PROFIT IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rexhall Industries Inc., a Santa Clarita motor-home maker, reported a sharp 
increase in earnings on a 79% gain in revenue in its first quarter ended March 
31. 
</P>
<P>
 Rexhall earned $520,000 on $10.3 million in revenue in the latest quarter, in 
contrast with a $137,000 profit on $5.78 million in revenue a year earlier. The 
company attributed its improved results to new motor-home styles and a stronger 
economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
