ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; COMMENTS SOUGHT ON WATER RATE HIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is seeking public comments on a proposed 6% water rate increase that 
the City Council is expected to vote on in June. 
</P>
<P>
 To voice opinions and concerns, residents are invited to attend a meeting at 7 
p.m. Thursday at the Fullerton Senior Multi-Service Center, at 340 W. 
Commonwealth. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting is hosted by the Fullerton Energy Resource Management Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 All comments will be considered by the council, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The water rate increase for next year has been proposed to cover operating 
costs for the city's water system. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials said that if the proposal is adopted, further increases would 
still be needed over a period of years. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 738-3177.MIMI KO 
