<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; HOME-PURCHASING ASSISTANCE AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 People interested in purchasing homes in the city might qualify for the 
county's First-Time Homebuyers Program. 
</P>
<P>
 The program provides qualified buyers with federal income tax credits that 
they can use to reduce their mortgage payments. 
</P>
<P>
 The credits give people who normally wouldn't be able to afford monthly house 
payments the tax breaks needed to pay a mortgage. 
</P>
<P>
 To qualify for the program, an applicant's household income must be less than 
$56,500 for a one or two-person family, and less than $64,975 for a family of 
three or more people, said Lee Whittenberg, the Seal Beach planning director. 
</P>
<P>
 The purchase price of a home must be less than $225,900, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the county's Housing and Redevelopment Office at 
(714) 568-4199.SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
