<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; RESIDENTS INVITED TO BUDGET STUDY SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials are encouraging residents to attend a series of budget study 
sessions this month and in June to see how $60 million in taxpayer money will 
be spent.  
</P>
<P>
 The first meeting was Monday and will be followed by sessions on May 23, June 
9 and June 13 in the City Council chambers at City Hall.All of the meetings are 
scheduled for 2 p.m. The seven-member City Council will review the budget page 
by page at the sessions. 
</P>
<P>
 The city is working on a plan to close a $3-million deficit in its 1994-95 
budget. City Manager Kevin J. Murphy laid off seven city workers on May 1 and 
has proposed the elimination of 26 other positions that are vacant or will 
become vacant. 
</P>
<P>
 Five police officers, a fire captain and the director of the Marine Department 
were among those let go. 
</P>
<P>
 At the June 13 meeting, the city will also hold a public hearing at which 
residents can express their concerns to their elected officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The council is tentatively scheduled to adopt the budget at the June 27 
meeting, the last one before the end of the fiscal year. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 644-3000.BOB ELSTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
