<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 MARK TAPER FORUM-BRED PLAYS WIN TOP TONY NODS; AWARDS: 'TWILIGHT: LOS 
ANGELES, 1992,' 'THE KENTUCKY CYCLE' AND 'ANGELS IN AMERICA: PERESTROIKA' ARE 
AMONG THE FOUR BEST PLAY CONTENDERS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON SHIRLEY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mark Taper Forum co-produced three of the four productions nominated for 
best play in this year's Tony Award competition. Nominations for the annual 
Broadway awards were announced in New York Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 "Angels in America: Perestroika," "The Kentucky Cycle" and "Twilight: Los 
Angeles, 1992" all went to Broadway after successful productions at the Taper. 
The fourth nominee in that category is Arthur Miller's "Broken Glass." 
</P>
<P>
 The new Stephen Sondheim-James Lapine musical, "Passion," received 10 
nominations -- the most garnered by any one show. "Disney's Beauty and the 
Beast" and "She Loves Me" placed second in total number of awards, with nine 
each. 
</P>
<P>
 "Angels in America: Perestroika" received six nominations. "The Kentucky 
Cycle" got three, while "Twilight: Los Angeles, 1992" won two. 
</P>
<P>
 In three categories, the Tony nomination committee unanimously requested a 
reduction in the number of nominees from the standard four, but in two of those 
categories the request was denied by the Tony Administration Subcommittee. 
</P>
<P>
 The awards will be presented June 12. 
</P>
<P>
 The complete list of nominees: 
</P>
<P>
 * Play: "Angels in America: Perestroika" by Tony Kushner; "Broken Glass" by 
Arthur Miller; "The Kentucky Cycle" by Robert Schenkkan; "Twilight: Los 
Angeles, 1992" by Anna Deavere Smith. 
</P>
<P>
 * Musical: "A Grand Night for Singing"; "Disney's Beauty and the Beast"; 
"Cyrano -- The Musical"; "Passion." 
</P>
<P>
 * Revival/Play: "Abe Lincoln in Illinois," "An Inspector Calls," "Medea," 
"Timon of Athens." 
</P>
<P>
 * Revival/Musical: "Carousel," "Damn Yankees," "Grease," "She Loves Me." 
</P>
<P>
 * Book of a Musical: Walter Bobbie, "A Grand Night for Sining"; Linda 
Woolverton, "Disney's Beauty and the Beast"; Koen Van Dijk, "Cyrano -- The 
Musical"; James Lapine, "Passion." 
</P>
<P>
 * Original Score: Alan Menken, Howard Ashman & Tim Rice, "Disney's Beauty and 
the Beast"; Ad Van Dijk, Koen Van Dijk, Peter Reeves, Sheldon Harnick, "Cyrano 
-- The Musical"; Stephen Sondheim, "Passion." 
</P>
<P>
 * Director/Musical: Scott Ellis, "She Loves Me"; Nicholas Hytner, "Carousel"; 
James Lapine, "Passion"; Robert Jess Roth, Disney's "Beauty and the Beast." 
</P>
<P>
 * Director/Play: Stephen Daldry, "An Inspector Calls"; Gerald Gutierrez, "Abe 
Lincoln in Illinois"; Michael Langham, "Timon of Athens"; George C. Wolfe, 
"Angels in America: Perestroika." 
</P>
<P>
 * Leading Actor/Play: Brian Bedford, "Timon of Athens"; Christopher Plummer, 
"No Man's Land"; Stephen Spinella, "Angels in America: Perestroika"; Sam 
Waterston, "Abe Lincoln in Illinois." 
</P>
<P>
 * Leading Actress/Play: Nancy Marchand, "Black Comedy"; Diana Rigg, "Medea"; 
Joan Rivers, "Sally Marr . . . and her escorts"; Anna Deavere Smith, "Twilight: 
Los Angeles, 1992." 
</P>
<P>
 * Leading Actor/Musical: Boyd Gaines, "She Loves Me"; Victor Garber, "Damn 
Yankees"; Terrence Mann, Disney's "Beauty and the Beast"; Jere Shea, "Passion." 
</P>
<P>
 * Leading Actress/Musical: Susan Egan, Disney's "Beauty and the Beast"; Dee 
Hoty, "The Best Little Whorehouse Goes Public"; Judy Kuhn, "She Loves Me"; 
Donna Murphy, "Passion." 
</P>
<P>
 * Featured Actor/Play: Larry Bryggman, "Picnic"; David Marshall Grant, "Angels 
in America: Perestroika"; Gregory Itzin, "The Kentucky Cycle"; Jeffrey Wright, 
"Angels in America: Perestroika." 
</P>
<P>
 * Featured Actress/Play: Jane Adams, "An Inspector Calls"; Debra Monk, 
"Picnic"; Jeanne Paulsen, "The Kentucky Cycle"; Anne Pitoniak, "Picnic." 
</P>
<P>
 * Featured Actor/Musical: Tom Aldredge, "Passion"; Gary Beach, Disney's 
"Beauty and the Beast"; Jarrod Emick, "Damn Yankees"; Jonathan Freeman, "She 
Loves Me." 
</P>
<P>
 * Featured Actress/Musical: Marcia Lewis, "Grease"; Sally Mayes, "She Loves 
Me"; Marin Mazzie, "Passion"; Audra Ann McDonald, "Carousel." 
</P>
<P>
 * Scenic Design: Bob Crowley, "Carousel"; Peter J. Davison, "Medea"; Ian 
MacNeil, "An Inspector Calls"; Tony Walton, "She Loves Me." 
</P>
<P>
 * Costume Design: David Charles and Jane Greenwood, "She Loves Me"; Jane 
Greenwood, "Passion"; Ann Hould-Ward, "Disney's Beauty and the Beast"; Yan Tax, 
"Cyrano -- The Musical." 
</P>
<P>
 * Lighting Design: Beverly Emmons, "Passion"; Jules Fisher, "Angels in 
America: Perestroika"; Rick Fisher, "An Inspector Calls"; Natasha Katz, 
"Disney's Beauty and the Beast." 
</P>
<P>
 * Choreography: Jeff Calhoun, "Grease"; Sir Kenneth MacMillan, "Carousel"; Rob 
Marshall, "Damn Yankees"; Rob Marshall, "She Loves Me." 
</P>
